				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">i'd suggest getting at max spell range and sining w/out LoS...</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
I don't think this is always the best advice.  If you are out of mobs LoS, they are out of yours.  If you get a resisted lull, you don't if it was a crit fail with agro until you see mobs charging you.  I generally try to get as far away as I can while still in LoS in order to see if I got agro from a lull resist.  That way, I can fade right away and try again.  On the other hand, I virtually never use lull anymore, since most mobs are immune or too high level.  Mez or snare splitting seems to much better in my experience.
<br />
